recordings.rmk:
Flew up from a privet hedge as I walked up. Landed within 5m of me and repeated the common call note for over a minute until I walked on.

# Habitat #
29-acre estate centrally located in Oxford, MS consisting of antebellum home surrounded by lawns and adjacent forest. Privet hedges and small thickets divide the grounds into distinct lawn units. Bordered on all sides by mature oak-hickory forest. Forest edge consists of oak spp, hickory spp, red cedar, mulberry, with understory along the edge dominated by privet (Ligustrum sp.). Grounds around the house include isolated trees and manicured hedges. A path from the end of the parking area leads northward ~1 km through the forest to the northern edge of the property abutting the University of Mississippi campus.

# Editing #
Audacity high-pass filter with 6 dB rolloff at 2 kHz

recordings.loc: Chicago, Cook County, Illinois
recordings.rmk:
4 cardinals were moving between trees and grass underneath the trees and calling to each other rapidly as they did.  They also seemed to search near a parked car by the curb for a few moments.  They also perched briefly on a nearby fence while moving between the trees and ground.

At least one of these cardinals found food or a bit of material, and flew into a tree with it.  The other cardinals went back to the trees soon after.  They were calling the entire time.

There was traffic nearby, which got picked up in my recording.
